	  <table width="642" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr>
          <td background="/newimages/backgrounds/middlecolumn_black.gif" valign="top"> 
              
            <!--First page-->
            <!--First page-->
            <!--First page-->
            <table width="491" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
              <tr>
                <td background="/newimages/articles/resize.gif" valign="top"><img src="/newimages/articles/blueborder.gif" width="1" height="86"></td>
                <td background="/newimages/articles/resize.gif" valign="top"> 
                  <img src="/php-bin/getimage.inc?id=98572"></td>
                <td valign="top" bgcolor="#000000"><img src="/newimages/misc/85border.gif" width="3" height="86"></td>
                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top" width="100%"> 
                  <TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#000000" height="40">
                    <TR> 
                      <TD nowrap class="smalltext" height="21">&nbsp;&nbsp;<SPAN class="bluebolded">Victim: </SPAN>Team Strike Force&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
                    </TR>
                    <TR> 
                      <TD nowrap class="smalltext" height="21">&nbsp;&nbsp;<SPAN class="bluebolded">Position: </SPAN>Creator&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
                    </TR>
                    <TR> 
                      <TD nowrap class="smalltext" height="21">&nbsp;&nbsp;<SPAN class="bluebolded">Company: </SPAN> <A href="http://www.strikeforcecenter.com7" class="brightlinks">Xtreme Gaming</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
                    </TR>
                    <TR> 
                      <TD nowrap class="smalltext" height="22">&nbsp;&nbsp;<SPAN class="bluebolded">Subject: </SPAN>life, the universe, everything&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
                    </TR>
                  </TABLE>
              </tr>
            </table>
            <TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
              <TR> 
                <TD><IMG src="/newimages/misc/492blueborder.gif" width="492" height="1"></TD>
              </TR>
            </TABLE>
            <TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="12">
              <TR valign="top"> 
                <TD class="smalltext">The Strike Force mod is becoming more and more popular, so we thought we'd take the team hostage for a short while so they could answer our questions. Here's part two of the interview, or if you missed part one then <A HREF="http://www.mgon.com/interviews.phtml?id=86350&language=en">click here</A>.</TD>
              </TR>
            </TABLE>
            <TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="12">
              <TR> 
                <TD> 
                  <SPAN class="Headline">Matt Sobotka</SPAN>
                  <P> <b>Could you please briefly introduce yourself, and tell us what it is you do on the Strike Force Project?</b><br />
My name is Matt Sobotka.  I've been playing games all my life and I've always been interested in how they worked.  I'm currently a level designer and texture artist for Strike Force.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>What made you want to become involved in game/mod development in the first place?</b><br />
I wanted to get involved with making mods because of the mod community.  These people work with whatever free time they have to create mods without pay because they love doing it.   That really inspired me and it’s the best feeling in the world when someone says they enjoyed your work.  This is definitely a career I plan on continuing.  <br />
<br />
I used to work on a single player total conversion for Unreal called Stone Killer.  It was a mob based game that I thought would be a big hit, but the team fell apart with not having enough free time so the game never was finished  :(<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Is game design a career you plan on continuing?</b><br />
I always wanted to do a massive multiplayer war game.  With the next generation game engines coming out that is very possible to do.   I personally can't wait for Unreal 2 :)<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Do you think your involvement with Strike Force will be able to open doors in the future in the way we've seen with Minh Lee from Counter Strike?</b><br />
I definitely think that working on Strike Force will open up new doors for me.  Everyone on the team works their butts off and it shows.  We have a lot of professional quality work going into Strike Force and hopefully game companies will notice that.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>What's your favorite map/feature in Strike Force?</b><br />
My favorite feature in Strike Force, as of now, is Escape mode. It creates a necessity for team work in order to reach the escape point. I personally like my map Austria the best haha<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>What's your favorite game ever?</b><br />
My favorite game ever would have to be....hmmm....there are so many. I personally loved Deus Ex because of the immersiveness of the world that it creates and how the story can change depending on what you do.  I also loved the replay value of the game. When I played it the 2nd time around the story was a lot different because I chose different routes to go than the ones I chose the first time I played.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Which development house do you admire the most?</b><br />
The development house that I admire the most would have to be EPIC.  They create some great games and the easiest to use tools and editors out there.  I don't know what I'd be doing if Unreal ED wasn't around :)<br />
</P>
                </TD>
              </TR>
            </TABLE>
